2006-08-02  Martin Bartosch  <m.bartosch@cynops.de>

	* certnanny: completely rewrote CA certificate chaining function

2006-06-07  Joerg Schneider <js@joergschneider.com>

	* certnanny: release version 0.8

2006-05-17  Thomas Thiele <thomas.thiele@db.com>

	* certnanny: Windows Certifcate Store support
	
2006-05-05  Joerg Schneider <js@joergschneider.com>

	* certnanny: added support for OpenSSL 0.9.8

	* certnanny: fixed a bug that the warnexpiry hook would be called when
	  a certificate is valid for less than autorenew_days days. Now the
	  warnexpiry hook is _only_ called when a certificate is valid for less
	  than warnexpiry_days.

	* certnanny: OpenSSL keystore: fixed a wrong default value for keytype
	  (PKCS8) introduced in 0.7. Correct default value: OpenSSL

	* certnanny: improved log format and made all (non-fatal error)
	  messages honor the loglevel. Introduced loglevel 5 (debug scep).

	* certnanny: added new option scepchecksubjectname, which activates a
	  subject name check (-C) supported by newer sscep versions
	
	* certnanny: --help print version number

	* certnanny: README and manual page create with pod2text/pod2man from
	  make

2006-04-20  Joerg Schneider <js@joergschneider.com>

	* certnanny: added Java keystore support

